  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Fluoxetine action on cerebral connectivity changes in acute ischemic stroke patients
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      In this placebo-controlled study, using functional resting state MRI, the investigators aim
      to investigate cerebral connectivity changes induced by fluoxetine given once a day for 90
      days, in stroke patients with a moderate to severe motor deficit.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
